From 8e8ac0e6937e1b3eff1b8af0a898de6eae527916 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 21:51:13 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 13/17] task4: multi-attempt evidence path + consolidator
 config fields

verify_note gains an additive path for evidence.attempts lists (used by
framework-authored consolidated notes): every cited attempt must be a
real scored one and every quoted score must match the store; creator
matching is skipped for aggregates; a proven mismatch beats an
unresolvable entry regardless of order. group_notes Rule 1 now unions
on attempt-set intersection so a new duplicate groups with a note that
cites a superset. Single-attempt behavior byte-identical.

agents.gate_consolidator_model (None = off) and
agents.gate_consolidator_timeout added next to publication_gate.

Reviewed single-pass, approved. 716 passed, 73 gate tests unmodified.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
